  "body": "So far, no meaningful warnings were issued for the following:\r\n\r\n## 1. Importing shap and directly accessing plots submodule\r\n\r\nThe following will throw a ModuleNotFound error about the `plots` submodule if `matplotlib` is not available and work fine otherwise\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport shap\r\nshap.plots \r\n```\r\n\r\nThis PR substitutes a `plots` object that will throw warnings once attributes are accessed, if `matplotlib` is unavailable.\r\n\r\n## 2. Directly importing shap.plots \r\n\r\nThe following will throw a rather cryptic exception rather than stating that matplotlib isn't available\r\n\r\n```python3\r\nimport shap.plots \r\n```\r\n\r\nThis PR simply tries to import `matplotlib` as soon as `plots` is imported and throws if the former isn't available.\r\n\r\n## Impact\r\n\r\nThe missing warnings might be (partially) responsible for confusion in https://github.com/slundberg/shap/issues/1975",
